commit 6b8d040d3cedc334bff0e6c4ecd692cc207ebbbf
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 12:47:10 2026 -0400

    test(conference)(section-skip): cover every skip + the present-but-empty hard-error

    Branch 4.2: pin the section-skip gating (4.1) from the outside and prove
    items stay strict.

    conference-detail.test.tsx — a `section-skip` block renders to string with
    each gate independently exercised: empty speakers/seminars omit only their
    own section; an absent `mapEmbedUrl` drops the iframe but keeps the hotels
    column (and vice-versa); both absent drops the whole `MapSection`; an absent
    `registrationUrl`/`scheduleUrl` drops the register/schedule buttons. Then the
    two launch shapes: `2026` (RegFox-only) = hero + register + FAQ with no empty
    sections, and `2025` (cancelled) = hero + FAQ only, EN+FR.

    schema.test.ts — a `Hotel present-but-empty hard-error` block proves skip is
    section-level, not item-level: a *present* hotel with a blank/absent required
    bilingual `name`, or a half-filled present `note`, fails strict (publish)
    decode; a fully-populated hotel publishes. Tolerance is for an absent list,
    never a half-built item (the both-locales `Text` invariant lives in the
    schema, never the component).

